Following the Syntax and non-deprecated method exactly, my attempt to change the S3 bucket lifecycle policy to include multipart uploads is as follows:

```
response = client.put_bucket_lifecycle_configuration(
        Bucket=bucket.name,
        LifecycleConfiguration={
            'Rules': [
                {

                    'ID': 'Automatic Expiration of Failed Multipart Uploads',
                    'Prefix': '',
                    'Status': 'Enabled',

                    'AbortIncompleteMultipartUpload': {
                        'DaysAfterInitiation': 7
                    }
                },
            ]
        }
    )
```

Regardless this always throws `Unknown parameter in LifecycleConfiguration.Rules[0]: "AbortIncompleteMultipartUpload", must be one of: Expiration, ID, Prefix, Status, Transitions, NoncurrentVersionTransitions, NoncurrentVersionExpiration`. The validation for the command doesn't know about this parameter.

Refer to https://github.com/Azure/azure-cli/pull/6392
This is a task to undo the PR submitted above.

